  "title": "E-COMMERCE MANAGER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Develop, execute, and oversee integrated digital marketing strategies to promote Chinese language learning resources across local and international markets.</p></li><li><p>Manage and optimize digital touchpoints, including websites, social media channels, email marketing, and e-commerce platforms, to ensure consistent brand presence and performance.</p></li><li><p>Drive brand awareness, qualified traffic acquisition, and sustained customer engagement through data-driven online initiatives.</p></li><li><p>Monitor, analyze, and interpret website and campaign performance using analytics tools (e.g. Google Analytics) to generate actionable insights.</p></li><li><p>Continuously optimize digital campaigns, funnels, and media spend to maximize return on investment (ROI) and marketing efficiency.</p></li><li><p>Enhance user experience (UX) and conversion performance across online platforms through testing, optimization, and user behavior analysis.</p></li><li><p>Stay abreast of evolving e-commerce trends, digital marketing innovations, and emerging technologies, translating insights into scalable business opportunities.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Job Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Bachelor’s degree or higher in Marketing, E-Commerce, Business Administration, or a related discipline.</p></li><li><p>At least <strong>3 years of relevant professional experience</strong> in digital marketing, e-commerce operations, or performance marketing, with a demonstrated track record of results.</p></li><li><p>Strong understanding of end-to-end online marketing strategies, including traffic acquisition, conversion optimisation, and e-commerce operations.</p></li><li><p>Hands-on experience with mainstream digital marketing, analytics, and e-commerce platforms (e.g. Google Analytics, Meta Ads Manager, Google Ads, Shopify or equivalent tools).</p></li><li><p>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to interpret data, identify trends, and make informed, data-driven decisions.</p></li><li><p>Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to articulate ideas clearly to both internal and external stakeholders.</p></li><li><p>Ability to manage multiple priorities independently in a fast-paced, results-oriented environment.</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with the <strong>Chinese language learning ecosystem or education-related content</strong>.</p></li></ul>",
